Victor Oshioke, media aide to Adams Oshiomhole, former national chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), has revealed that his principal will announce his intention to contest the presidency on Wednesday. This was contained in a statement issued on Tuesday. Oshioke stated that the former Edo governor will make an official declaration at 3pm at the Cyprian Ekwensi Centre for Arts and Culture in Abuja. Also Read: 2023: How Power Can Shift To South, Shehu Sani Reveals “The formal declaration of Comrade Adams Aliyu Oshiomhole to contest for the office of President, Federal Republic of Nigeria, in the 2023 general election on the platform of the All Progressives Congress which was postponed has now been rescheduled, after extensive consultations,” the statement reads. “We apologise for the short notice and hope that your love for Comrade Adams Aliyu Oshiomhole will motivate you to attend, irrespective of any unforeseen constraints.” He added that the event was scheduled to hold on an earlier date, but was later postponed for further consultations.